I"6<p>Just like <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/promises-streamline-asynchronous-processing">promises streamline asynchronous processing</a>, so do streams formalize input-output communication between various components of a software system. By framing this task as a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/tools-for-thought-interface-users-with-knowledge">channel through which information</a> can be <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/dynamical-systems-have-a-certain-anatomy">emitted</a> and consumed, streams make I/O more manageable.</p>
